      <Refines>HL-MAP-2.3</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>Mapping shall progress to provide a usable partial map within 5 minutes under typical conditions. If full mapping is not feasible within 5 minutes, the system shall provide partial map status and continue mapping in the background, with progress indicators available to the operator.</Content>
  </Requirement>
  <Requirement ID="LL-PLAN-3.1" type="FR">
    <ID>LL-PLAN-3.1</ID>
    <Name>Path Planning Algorithm</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-PLAN-3.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>The planner shall compute a path from the current position to the target using an admissible algorithm (e.g., A*) on the internal map, returning a sequence of waypoints. Planning shall complete within 100 ms per planning instance, assuming a static map snapshot.</Content>
  </Requirement>
  <Requirement ID="LL-RUN-4.1" type="FR">
    <ID>LL-RUN-4.1</ID>
    <Name>Return to Start Navigation</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-RUN-4.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>The robot shall navigate back to the designated start position after exploration using the latest available map and path plan, re-planning if obstacles are encountered, and ensuring obstacle avoidance throughout the path.</Content>
  </Requirement>
  <Requirement ID="LL-RUN-4.2" type="FR">
    <ID>LL-RUN-4.2</ID>
    <Name>Second Exploration Run</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-RUN-4.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>The robot shall perform a second exploration run after the first, reusing the map where possible and adjusting the path to improve coverage efficiency and reduce redundant traversal.</Content>
  </Requirement>
  <Requirement ID="LL-RUN-4.3" type="FR">
    <ID>LL-RUN-4.3</ID>
    <Name>Efficient Path Execution</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-RUN-4.3</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>The second run shall follow the most efficient path to the target as determined by the planner, with minimal backtracking, and shall adapt the path if real-time obstacle information indicates a better route.</Content>
  </Requirement>
  <Requirement ID="LL-RELIAB-5.1" type="NFR">
    <ID>LL-RELIAB-5.1</ID>
    <Name>Collision Avoidance Robustness</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-RELIAB-5.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>The system shall prevent collisions with walls and obstacles by maintaining a safe stopping distance, applying emergency braking as needed, and signaling a fault if a collision risk cannot be mitigated in time.</Content>
  </Requirement>
  <Requirement ID="LL-RELIAB-5.2" type="NFR">
    <ID>LL-RELIAB-5.2</ID>
    <Name>Fault Tolerance and Degradation</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-RELIAB-5.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>The system shall detect sensor or actuator faults, switch to redundant or fallback components if available, validate inputs from degraded sensors, and degrade gracefully without complete system failure.</Content>
  </Requirement>
  <Requirement ID="LL-INTERF-6.1" type="FR">
    <ID>LL-INTERF-6.1</ID>
    <Name>Sensor Data Processing</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-6.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>The system shall process sensor data according to the sensor data interface description, perform filtering and normalization, and produce a timely, consistent measurement stream suitable for the map and planner components.</Content>
  </Requirement>
  <Requirement ID="LL-INTERF-6.2" type="FR">
    <ID>LL-INTERF-6.2</ID>
    <Name>Actuator Command Interface</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-6.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>The system shall send motor commands to actuators via the motor interface, await acknowledgement within a defined timeout, and validate command formats before dispatch to ensure safe actuator operation.</Content>
  </Requirement>
</Requirements>


